OL,6,GIt's been another rotten week for the
OL,7,GBBC.  But it's also the start of a
OL,8,Gweek which could remind the BBC's
OL,9,Gnatural supporters of one of its key
OL,10,Gstrengths.
OL,12,FThe resignation of the chairman came
OL,13,Fafter weeks of speculation over his
OL,14,Ffuture.
OL,16,FOf course, the chairman is not
OL,17,Fresponsible for editorial decisions.
OL,18,FBut even the impression that he may
OL,19,Fhave been a political appointee is
OL,20,Fdamaging.
OL,3,CBBC: dividing public opinion and
OL,4,Cbringing people together
