OL,6,FFor those who want to believe there
OL,7,Fis right wing bias in all of the
OL,8,Fmainstream media, it seemed like
OL,9,Fproof.
OL,11,FOthers worried the chairman was being
OL,12,Fsent in to "sort out" the BBC by
OL,13,FBoris Johnson ` just as they worried
OL,14,Fthat the planned privatisation of
OL,15,FChannel 4 was also about taming
OL,16,Fjournalism.
OL,18,FBut there is a distinction between
OL,19,Fwanting to ensure that public sector
OL,20,Fappointments are made in the
OL,21,Fappropriate way and accusations of
OL,22,Fbias in journalism.
OL,3,CBBC: dividing public opinion and
OL,4,Cbringing people together
