OL,6,FAs a general rule, those who want to
OL,7,Fsee bias will always find evidence to
OL,8,Ffit their conclusion.
OL,10,FAnd those with a long memory know
OL,11,Fthat governments of all hues have
OL,12,Faccused the BBC of bias against them
OL,13,Fat various points in time.
OL,15,FWhat really matters is what the
OL,16,Fbroader public think. This is why it
OL,17,Fis so important to ensure the
OL,18,Fchairman enjoys full public
OL,19,Fconfidence. He is a figurehead for
OL,20,Fthe corporation's independence.
OL,3,CBBC: dividing public opinion and
OL,4,Cbringing people together
