OL,6,FBut against this row, a significant
OL,7,Fpart of the public are looking
OL,8,Fforward to Saturday and the
OL,9,FCoronation.
OL,11,FIn 1953, of course, support for the
OL,12,Fmonarchy was close to universal.
OL,14,FToday polls indicate that significant
OL,15,Fnumbers are either not interested or
OL,16,Fwant an elected head of state. (That
OL,17,Fis especially true outside England.)
OL,19,FSomehow the BBC has to do what many
OL,20,Fwould expect of it at a moment in
OL,21,Fhistory.
OL,3,CBBC: dividing public opinion and
OL,4,Cbringing people together
